<heading id="D0A68186FFBFFF817DCCFBBBFC83FB80" box="[505,878,1109,1133]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="2" pageNumber="1879" reason="2">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D69FFBFFF817E7FFBBBFC83FB80" authority="Curran, 1934" authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1934" box="[586,878,1109,1133]" class="Insecta" family="Richardiidae" genus="Beebeomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1879" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B925EAF8FFBFFF817E7FFBBBFD3DFB80" bold="true" box="[586,720,1109,1133]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1879">Beebeomyia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC04B1BFFBFFF817EEDFBBBFC83FB80" author="Curran CH" box="[728,878,1109,1133]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1879" pagination="271 - 284" refId="ref4955" refString="Curran CH. 1934. Family Otitidae - the pictured-wing flies. In: Curran CH, editor. The families and genera of North American Diptera. New York: The Ballou Press; p. 271 - 284." type="book chapter" year="1934">Curran, 1934</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34B6561FFBFFF807CE1FB70FF2AFEED" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="1880" pageId="2" pageNumber="1879" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEE36EAFFBFFF817CE1FB70FEADFB58" blockId="2.[212,1172,1182,1693]" box="[212,320,1182,1205]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1879">
<heading id="D0A68186FFBFFF817CE1FB70FEADFB58" box="[212,320,1182,1205]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="1879" reason="5">
<emphasis id="B925EAF8FFBFFF817CE1FB70FEADFB58" box="[212,320,1182,1205]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1879">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEE36EAFFBFFF817CE1FB2BFD7DFA11" blockId="2.[212,1172,1182,1693]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1879">
This genus belongs to the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D69FFBFFF817EA7FB2BFCCEFB30" box="[658,803,1221,1245]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1879" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Richardiinae">Richardiinae</taxonomicName>
and can be recognised by the following combination of characters: head little or no longer than high; frons twice as long as wide, ocellar triangle very long, the anterior ocellus near the middle of the frons, scarcely hollowed above; frons flat, level with eyes; basal antennal segment short, more or less hidden; one pair of frontal setae opposite the ocellar seta; postocellar setae extremely weak; outer vertical seta as strong as inner vertical seta. Thorax with middle portion of the propleura pubescent only; the following setae present: 1 postpronotal, 2 notopleural, 1 anepisternal, 0–1 presutural supra-alar; 1 postsutural supra-alar; 2 dorsocentral (except one pair in 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D69FFBFFF817F48FA2BFC0EFA31" authorityName="Two" baseAuthorityName="Hennig" baseAuthorityYear="1937" box="[893,995,1476,1500]" class="Insecta" family="Richardiidae" genus="Beebeomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1879" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="senilis">
<emphasis id="B925EAF8FFBFFF817F48FA2BFC0EFA31" box="[893,995,1476,1500]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1879">B. senilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 1 postalar; 1 intra-postalar; acrostichal setae absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEE36EAFFBFFF807CCBF9EAFF2AFEED" blockId="2.[212,1172,1182,1693]" lastBlockId="3.[144,1103,168,256]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="1880" pageId="2" pageNumber="1879">
All femora moderately slender with spiny ventral setae on apical half, usually reduced or sometimes absent on the fore femur, always present on mid and hind legs; hind femur not more swollen than others; vein Sc ending near the apex of R 
<subScript id="17D534AFFFBFFF8178B7F9A0FB61F9B3" attach="left" box="[1154,1164,1614,1630]" fontSize="7" pageId="2" pageNumber="1879">1</subScript>
; crossvein r-m slightly before or at middle of the discal cell; crossveins r-m and dmcu further apart than length of dm-cu; cell bcu rounded to apex; vein A 
<subScript id="17D534AFFFBFFF817817F963FBC1F970" attach="left" box="[1058,1068,1677,1693]" fontSize="7" pageId="2" pageNumber="1879">1</subScript>
+ CuA 
<subScript id="17D534AFFFBFFF8178BFF963FB79F970" attach="left" box="[1162,1172,1677,1693]" fontSize="7" pageId="2" pageNumber="1879">2</subScript>
reaching margin at least as a fold; R 
<subScript id="17D534AFFFBEFF807E6DFF5DFD97FF2E" attach="left" box="[600,634,179,195]" fontSize="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">2+3</subScript>
straight, not undulate; male costa not expanded. First abdominal segment narrowed at base, the apical portion of abdomen oval.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34B6561FFBEFF807CA5FEC6FBBDFB51" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880" type="key">
<paragraph id="8BEE36EAFFBEFF807CA5FEC6FCF1FEAD" blockId="3.[144,796,295,320]" box="[144,796,295,320]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">
<heading id="D0A68186FFBEFF807CA5FEC6FCF1FEAD" box="[144,796,295,320]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880" reason="5">
<emphasis id="B925EAF8FFBEFF807CA5FEC6FCF1FEAD" bold="true" box="[144,796,295,320]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">
Key to species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D69FFBEFF807D63FEC9FE31FED2" authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1934" box="[342,476,295,319]" class="Insecta" family="Richardiidae" genus="Beebeomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B925EAF8FFBEFF807D63FEC9FE31FED2" bold="true" box="[342,476,295,319]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">Beebeomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Neotropical region
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<key id="FFC061DBFFBEFF807CA5FEB6FBBDFB51" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">
<paragraph id="8BEE36EAFFBEFF807CA5FEB6FBA2FE22" blockId="3.[144,1103,344,463]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">
<keyLead id="30A095DFFFBEFF807CA5FEB6FBA2FE22" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">
<keyStep id="30A52E4FFFBEFF807CA5FEB6FBA2FE22" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">
1. Only one dorsocentral seta; thorax wholly black (including mesonotum and pleuron); wing with apical spot (
<collectingCountry id="F346767AFFBEFF807E15FE99FDBBFE62" box="[544,598,375,399]" name="Peru" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">Peru</collectingCountry>
) ....................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D69FFBEFF807FB4FE96FF0DFE42" authority="(Hennig) Two" authorityName="Two" baseAuthorityName="Hennig" baseAuthorityYear="1937" class="Insecta" family="Richardiidae" genus="Beebeomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="senilis">
<emphasis id="B925EAF8FFBEFF807FB4FE96FBA2FE62" bold="true" box="[897,1103,375,399]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">
<emphasis id="B925EAF8FFBEFF807FB4FE96FC08FE62" bold="true" box="[897,997,375,399]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">B. senilis</emphasis>
(Hennig)
</emphasis>
Two
</taxonomicName>
dorsocentral setae, with anterior pair smaller; thorax reddish or black, pleuron sometimes with yellow markings ............................................................ 2
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEE36EAFFBEFF807CA5FE09FBA2FD73" blockId="3.[144,1104,487,670]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">
<keyLead id="30A095DFFFBEFF807CA5FE09FBA2FD73" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">
<keyStep id="30A52E4FFFBEFF807CA5FE09FBA2FD73" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">
2. Mesoscutum largely black, postpronotal lobes yellow; pleura black with yellow stripe along hind margin of mesopleuron and extending to part of notopleuron; metapleural callus yellow; wing with large apical spot extending basal to middle of last section of vein M (
<collectingCountry id="F346767AFFBEFF807D80FDA9FE17FDB2" box="[437,506,583,607]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">Brazil</collectingCountry>
) ........................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D69FFBEFF807F1BFDA9FED1FD93" authority="(Hennig) Mesoscutum" authorityName="Mesoscutum" baseAuthorityName="Hennig" baseAuthorityYear="1937" class="Insecta" family="Richardiidae" genus="Beebeomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavimaculata">
<emphasis id="B925EAF8FFBEFF807F1BFDA9FBA2FDB2" bold="true" box="[814,1103,582,607]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">
<emphasis id="B925EAF8FFBEFF807F1BFDA9FC08FDB3" bold="true" box="[814,997,582,606]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">B. flavimaculata</emphasis>
(Hennig)
</emphasis>
Mesoscutum
</taxonomicName>
reddish or yellowish; wing with much smaller apical spot or none at all, otherwise differing ......................................................................................... 3
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEE36EAFFBEFF807CA5FD58FBA2FC40" blockId="3.[144,1104,694,941]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">
<keyLead id="30A095DFFFBEFF807CA5FD58FBA2FC40" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">
<keyStep id="30A52E4FFFBEFF807CA5FD58FBA2FC40" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">
3. Presutural supra-alar seta present; costal and subcostal cells dark brown; foreleg yellow including coxa to tarsomeres; male with inner and outer surstyli elongated of similar length in lateral view; distiphallus broad, membranous, basally with two rows of long yellow setae forming two combs; phallus coiled with strong setae along basal third; female aculeus nearly two times as long as wide, apex yellow sclerotised, triangular, nearly as long as wide (
<collectingCountry id="F346767AFFBEFF807E8BFCB8FCF8FC83" box="[702,789,854,878]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">Mexico</collectingCountry>
) ......................................... ................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D69FFBEFF807E3AFC98FC0BFC60" authority="Hernandez-Ortiz &amp; Aguirre" authorityName="Hernandez-Ortiz &amp; Aguirre" authorityYear="2015" box="[527,998,885,909]" class="Insecta" family="Richardiidae" genus="Beebeomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuxtlaensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B925EAF8FFBEFF807E3AFC98FC0BFC60" bold="true" box="[527,998,885,909]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">
<emphasis id="B925EAF8FFBEFF807E3AFC98FD4AFC60" bold="true" box="[527,679,885,909]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">B. tuxtlaensis</emphasis>
Hernández-Ortiz &amp; Aguirre
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2165783FFBEFF807FC3FC98FBBDFC60" box="[1014,1104,886,909]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Presutural supra-alar seta lacking; subcostal cells pale yellowish to hyaline ....... 4
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEE36EAFFBEFF807CA5FC2BFBBDFB51" blockId="3.[144,1104,965,1212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">
<keyLead id="30A095DFFFBEFF807CA5FC2BFBBDFB51" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">
<keyStep id="30A52E4FFFBEFF807CA5FC2BFBBDFB51" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">
4. Femora partly yellow, hind femur with brown distomedian ring; mid and hind tibiae brown; abdomen metallic blue with greenish sheen; mesonotum reddish; postpronotal lobe and posterior border of mesopleuron yellowish (
<collectingCountry id="F346767AFFBEFF807F96FBEBFC34FBF0" box="[931,985,1029,1053]" name="Peru" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">Peru</collectingCountry>
) .............. ............................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D69FFBEFF807F65FBCBFEEBFBB0" authority="(Hennig) Femora" authorityName="Femora" baseAuthorityName="Hennig" baseAuthorityYear="1937" class="Insecta" family="Richardiidae" genus="Beebeomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calligastra">
<emphasis id="B925EAF8FFBEFF807F65FBCBFBA2FBD0" bold="true" box="[848,1103,1060,1085]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">
<emphasis id="B925EAF8FFBEFF807F65FBCBFC08FBD1" bold="true" box="[848,997,1060,1084]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">B. calligastra</emphasis>
(Hennig)
</emphasis>
Femora
</taxonomicName>
wholly reddish yellow, tibiae and tarsi slightly paler; abdomen shinning black; mesonotum rusty reddish, with a broad, gently widening median whitish pollinose stripe, extending from the anterior margin to the scutellum; pleura and most of metanotum brown (
<collectingCountry id="F346767AFFBEFF807DDAFB4AFDA6FB51" box="[495,587,1188,1212]" name="Guyana" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">Guyana</collectingCountry>
) ..................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D69FFBEFF807F5CFB4BFBBDFB51" authority="(Cresson)" baseAuthorityName="Cresson" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[873,1104,1188,1212]" class="Insecta" family="Richardiidae" genus="Zeugma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palposa">
<emphasis id="B925EAF8FFBEFF807F5CFB4BFBAAFB51" bold="true" box="[873,1095,1188,1212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">
<emphasis id="B925EAF8FFBEFF807F5CFB4BFC32FB51" bold="true" box="[873,991,1188,1212]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1880">B. palposa</emphasis>
(Cresson
</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</key>
